						               													<description>Verkopft is a fast pacing card game from the publishing company Simon &amp;amp; Jan, released in June 2019.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It gained regional fame as the publishers decided to give away 700 units of this game for free to non-profit organizations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Verkopft is a game about speed and focus. Every card contains 4 different information:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     a background color&amp;#10;     a fruit&amp;#10;     a text&amp;#10;     a textcolor&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players must handle all these (partially conflicting) information under time pressure and name the information that is looked for in this round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game utilizes a psychologicial effect called the stroop effect. This effect describes a converting conflict within a human's brain when several conflicting information appear.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
